note.p:
Pub. L. 104–107, title V, § 531A(b), Feb. 12, 1996, 110 Stat. 731, provided that: “Section 22(d) of the Arms Export Control Act [subsec. (d) of this section], as added by subsection (a)— “(1) shall take effect on the 60th day following the date of the enactment of this Act [Feb. 12, 1996];
“(2) shall be applicable only to contracts made in implementation of sales made after such effective date; and
“(3) shall be implemented by revised procurement regulations, which shall be issued prior to such effective date.”
